query.result:
46 For neither rain, nor hail, nor snow 47 falls, nor dew, nor frost anymore above 48 than the staircase of three short steps;
49 thick clouds do not appear neither sparse, 50 nor flash, nor daughter of Taumante, 51 who from there often changes regions;
52 dry vapor does not surge forward more 53 than to the top of the three steps that I spoke of, 54 where has the vicar of Peter the plants.

55 Trembles perhaps more down little or much;
56 but for wind that in earth hides itself,
57 I do not know how, up here it never trembled.

91 Statius the people there still name me;
92 I sang of Thebes, and then of great Achilles;
93 but I fell on the way with the second pack.

